13. Kapoc         0.010  0.030  0.018  16-30 / 1.2  / 0.1   / 1300
14. Jute          0.005  0.025  0.018  27-53 / 1.5  / 0.3   / 1700-1800
15. Phormium      0.005  0.025  0.013
16. Pineapple Fib 0.003  0.013  0.006
A- BREAK LENGTH 3         C- WORK OF RUPTURE
B- ULTIMATE STRAIN %      D- INITIAL ELASTICITY
  
1 Handbook of Textile Fibers, Harris Research Lab
2 Ultimate means Individual Fibers
3 Length in Km - a fibers break length is a measurement that shows
how long a fiber would have to be to break under its own weight.
Usually measured in Kilometers.
  
