STRENGTH AND ELONGATION OF VARIOUS FIBERS1
  
FIBER:      A      B        C 2     D         E
Ramie	   5.42   7.34     66.0    99.0      4.6 (Yuenkang)
Ramie      5.88   6.73     60.6    91.0      4.2 (Kingkiang)
True Hemp 12.75   6.26     56.4    83.5      2.0
Flax      16.5    5.82     52.4    76.5      1.6
Jute      19.55   3.19     28.7    41.4      1.4
Cotton     2.10   2.74     24.6    36.9      9.8
Silk       1.27   3.76     34.0    46.3      16.3
Wool      15.00   2.06     18.5    24.6      40.9
  
A- DENIER           D- TENSILE STRENGTH
B- TENACITY         E- ELONGATION %
C- BREAK LENGTH 2
  
   1 Handbook of Textile Fibers pg 135
   2 Length in Km (see note 3 above)
